<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Extended 16-bar form. "33" root triads dominate. "333" D7 at key cadences.
- E7 (non-diatonic) → Em (③m). Eb → Am (②m) or Em. Bm² used at bar 7 for variety.
- LH always 3-4 notes open voicing; RH 2-note thirds/sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH G2 pedal point anchors the many G-chord returns.
- RH climbs to G5/B5 at bars 9/13 (the repeated phrase peak) then settles.
- Contrary motion bars 6-7: RH rises while LH steps down.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Two identical phrase halves (bars 1-8, 9-16). Second half builds higher in RH (G5-B5).
- Climax bar 9-10: RH at highest register. Final V7-I cadence bars 15-16.
-->
